From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alexander Schiffhauer <alexander.schiffhauer@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 18 May 2026 20:40:04 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] winewayland.drv: Add SNI StatusNotifierItem systray via libdbus.

Wayland has no equivalent of the X11 _NET_SYSTEM_TRAY XEmbed
protocol that winex11.drv uses for tray icons, so wine apps lose
their tray icon entirely on KDE Plasma 6, GNOME (with the
AppIndicator extension), waybar, and any other Wayland shell.

Implement the pSystrayDock* driver hooks against the
StatusNotifierItem D-Bus spec (KDE's freedesktop-pending standard
adopted by all the above shells).  Each icon registers an SNI
service via libdbus, exports the icon pixmap, and translates SNI
Activate/SecondaryActivate signals into WM_LBUTTONUP / WM_RBUTTONUP
messages on the Windows tray icon owner window.

Implementation lives in a new wayland_systray.c so it can be
reused by other Wayland drivers if desired.

Signed-off-by: Alexander Schiffhauer <alexander.schiffhauer@gmail.com>
